Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Zinedine Zidane has requested that Real Madrid go all out to land Manchester United midfielder Paul Pogba this summer, reports Marca. The France international has long been linked with a move to the Santiago Bernabeu. A window of rebuilding in the Spanish capital could now see a big-money deal pushed through, with Pogba prepared to take a pay cut in order to join Luka Jovic and Eden Hazard at the new-look Blancos. There are, however, indications thatl Madrid are not optimistic about signing him as Manchester United will not entertain any offers for their midfielder, according to AS.